<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Font Properties</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            margin: 30px;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        .font-family {
            font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        }

        .font-size-small {
            font-size: 14px;
        }

        .font-size-medium {
            font-size: 20px;
        }

        .font-size-large {
            font-size: 32px;
        }

        .font-weight-normal {
            font-weight: normal;
        }

        .font-weight-bold {
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .font-weight-number {
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .italic {
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .oblique {
            font-style: oblique;
        }

        .uppercase {
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .lowercase {
            text-transform: lowercase;
        }

        .capitalize {
            text-transform: capitalize;
        }

        .letter-spacing {
            letter-spacing: 4px;
        }

        .word-spacing {
            word-spacing: 12px;
        }

        .line-height {
            line-height: 2.5;
        }

        .underline {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .overline {
            text-decoration: overline;
        }

        .line-through {
            text-decoration: line-through;
        }

        .center {
            text-align: center;
        }

        .right {
            text-align: right;
        }

        .shadow {
            font-size: 28px;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px gray;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>CSS Font Properties</h1>

    <h2>1. Font Family</h2>
    <p class="font-family">
        This text uses the Georgia font family.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Font Size</h2>
    <p class="font-size-small">Small Text (14px)</p>
    <p class="font-size-medium">Medium Text (20px)</p>
    <p class="font-size-large">Large Text (32px)</p>

    <h2>3. Font Weight</h2>
    <p class="font-weight-normal">Normal Text</p>
    <p class="font-weight-bold">Bold Text</p>
    <p class="font-weight-number">Font Weight: 700</p>

    <h2>4. Font Style</h2>
    <p class="italic">Italic Text</p>
    <p class="oblique">Oblique Text</p>

    <h2>5. Text Transform</h2>
    <p class="uppercase">uppercase text</p>
    <p class="lowercase">LOWERCASE TEXT</p>
    <p class="capitalize">welcome to css</p>

    <h2>6. Letter Spacing</h2>
    <p class="letter-spacing">
        Letter Spacing Example
    </p>

    <h2>7. Word Spacing</h2>
    <p class="word-spacing">
        Word Spacing Example
    </p>

    <h2>8. Line Height</h2>
    <p class="line-height">
        CSS makes web pages beautiful and easy to read.
        Increasing the line height improves readability,
        especially when paragraphs are long.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Text Decoration</h2>
    <p class="underline">Underline</p>
    <p class="overline">Overline</p>
    <p class="line-through">Line Through</p>

    <h2>10. Text Alignment</h2>
    <p class="center">Center Aligned Text</p>
    <p class="right">Right Aligned Text</p>

    <h2>11. Text Shadow</h2>
    <p class="shadow">
        CSS Text Shadow
    </p>

</body>
</html>